reviews.review: Much better than I expected, upon a second viewing it got better, I enjoyed the lightsaber duels, the new force abilities shown in it, like a light side user (or so she thinks) using force lightning on the big screen! and force healing, nice additions to the new cannon. Plot twists were also pretty good, some were a bit forced though, but that's what plot twists are like sometimes. It certainly repairs the Sequels trilogy and you should watch it if you haven't already

Been a Star Wars fan since 1977. I’ve watched all the trilogies. This barely beat out any of the episodes 1-3.  JJ screwed the pooch. Not following the story line set out by George Lucas means this story line makes NO sense.  Would I go see it again?  Nope. Would I recommend watching?  Meh!  Only if you must!  Disney can do better than this. Look at PIXAR and MARVEL.  They have SNAFU’d the films. Thank goodness Jon Favreau rescued The Madalorian!
Honestly, the first trilogy was great. I have been disappointed since then.  The highlight was the acting by Adam Driver. He is outstanding.
I loved it! So much fun to have old characters woven in to the story.

The best of the recent trilogy. As a stand-alone movie - very solid. Exciting pacing and overall believable acting.  A bit put off by Carrie Fisher animation and the use of "spirit guides" proved a bit too much "Deus Ex Machina" - but overall - a very enjoyable popcorn movie.

Felt like a piecemeal. Doesn't have any consistency with the starwars universe, or what was installed in the previous movies of the new trilogy. Laughable character development. No emotional connection.
A little disappointed after all the hype (and hope) for this movie to be great.  Fight scene were ok, plot was slow, etc.  Also too Disney-esque.
Worth seeing if you've seen every other Star Wars movie. Exciting, a little hard to keep track of, but still a decent way to end the series.
Great graphics and good cast.  Movie is a bit long, but we really enjoyed it.
Good story, decent job rapping things up.
